|CKBStreet Samurai Hardware|000

|CK0Every Street Samurai routine depends on one or more signature implants.
The Cortex OS hosts the platform and is installed automatically when joining.
Rin Kade and Othra Veyr sell the remaining signature lines as they unlock from
GL2 through GL14.|000

|CKBIntegrated weapon systems|000
|CK0The right-eye Photon Targeting Suite supports Threat Scan and unlocks
Photon Lance at GL4. The left-shoulder Dorsal Tempest Driver becomes available
at GL8 for Micro-Missile Swarm and later coordinates Chrome Tempest. The torso
Thermal Exchange Manifold provides Cold Signal and unlocks Thermal Purge at
GL11. Older names such as Targeting Suite, Tempest Driver, and Coolant System
remain valid when speaking with the Cortex or a ripperdoc.|000

|CKBChoosing hardware|000
|CK0Engage a ripperdoc and inspect the signature catalog before buying. Each
entry shows its paired implant, internal location, strain, grade, Guild Level
requirement, and exact price. Buying places the hardware in your inventory;
installation is a separate confirmed procedure. The clinic refuses an implant
when its location conflicts or its strain would exceed current capacity.
Street Samurai signature hardware remains contract-locked: no ripperdoc can
install it in someone who is not a registered Street Samurai.|000

|CKBGrades|000
|CK0The grade order from weakest to strongest is Prototype, Street, Military,
and Ghost. Prototype is available first, with Street at GL7, Military at GL10,
and Ghost at GL13. A specific implant's own unlock can require a later Guild
Level.|000

|CK0Higher grades improve their paired firmware and built-in equipment
benefits, resist accumulated physical wear more effectively, and usually
consume more strain. Grade does not replace maintenance: even exceptional
hardware should be repaired and defragmented when its condition declines.|000

|CKBStrain and slots|000
|CK0Installed cyberware consumes strain capacity and occupies an internal
location. Character level, remort progress, and the Street Samurai contract
all contribute to capacity. Reaching Ronin-sama at Guild Level 16 provides a
substantial final capacity surge for installing new hardware or upgrading an
existing implant. Use cyberware or implants to review the complete internal
layout and live strain limit; dashboard shows Street Samurai implant load and
condition.|000

|CKBInspecting the loadout|000
|CK0Use implants for all installed internal equipment, cyberware for available
and occupied implant locations, dashboard for Street Samurai grade, integrity,
fragmentation, and runtime state, and samskills for missing required hardware.
Samhelp firmware contains the complete routine-to-implant map.|000
